                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3317: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-27T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 27, 1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. Your 35, March 26, 10 a.m. The Governor of Arica reports that Chilean and
                    Peruvian engineers have examined proposed ports at and north of Escritos; that
                    Chilean engineers made clear that Chile would not under any conditions permit a
                    Peruvian port at the mouth of the River San José; that the engineers
                    representing Peru, <pb facs="0893" n="757" xml:id="pg_757"/> who left Arica for
                    Lima this morning, did not indicate the nature of the recommendations which they
                    would make to President Leguia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
